  "prompt": "Did islam exist before prophet mohmmad?",
  "response": "No, Islam as a religion did not exist before the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him). Islam, which means \"submission to the will of Allah (God),\" was revealed to Prophet Muhammad in the 7th century CE in the Arabian Peninsula. The message of Islam, as conveyed through the Qur'an, was brought by Prophet Muhammad, who is considered the final prophet and messenger in Islam.\n\nHowever, Islam teaches that its core message of monotheism (belief in one God) and submission to God was the essence of previous prophets' teachings, such as Adam, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus (peace be upon them all). Muslims believe that these prophets were sent by Allah to guide their people, but over time, their original messages were altered or lost. Prophet Muhammad\u2019s mission was to restore and finalize this divine guidance for all of humanity. Thus, while the specific faith of Islam did not exist before Prophet Muhammad, its foundational principles align with the monotheistic teachings of earlier prophets.",
